      "comment": "PANIC (2) handy type with his hoof on the till. Can stalk the fast tempo again after finishing a close-up fourth over 1000m at Orange. Blinkers come off with the senior rider going on. Hard to hold out. RAVALLI (1) is a five-year-old gelding having his first run for the Rob Potter yard. Resumes after finishing a poor eleventh over 1200m at Morphettville. Goes well at the trip and can surprise fresh with the tongue-tie coming off. FEIRME PRINCE (4) was a month between runs with a close-up fifth over 1280m at Muswellbrook. Drops in weight and has an okay record at this course. SCOPICS (5) good fresh gelding who will relish the fast tempo.",
